Mutuku Mwangangi @PitzPitah Three  suspects linked to the death of a seven-month-old baby Ethan Muendo at Shalom Community Hospital in Machakos have been charged with manslaughter. Vincent Njau Nganga,  Odhiambo Kennedy and Katete Mutinda were charged before senior resident magistrate Irene Kahuya.They pleaded not guilty. Nganga is said to have been the clinician who prescribed the morphine overdose that killed the infant while, Odhiambo, is the pharmaceutical technologist who dispensed the drug. He also recommended the use of morphine injection because the facility had run out of syrup. Mutinda, a patient attendant, is said to have administered the injection. They were also charged with recklessness and negligence. The three were released on a Sh500,000 cash bail each with a surety of a similar amount pending mention of the case on May 23.